# Security Auditor — Bunyan

## Authentication

- Laravel Sanctum for API authentication
- Token expiration: 24 hours for web, configurable for API
- Rate limit login attempts: 5 per minute per IP
- Password requirements: min 8 chars, mixed case, number, symbol

## Authorization (RBAC)

- Every endpoint must document allowed roles
- Authorization via Laravel Policies and Gates
- Never trust role info from client request body
- All routes use appropriate middleware (`auth:sanctum`, role middleware)

### Role Matrix

| Role                  | Arabic           | Access Level                              |
| --------------------- | ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| admin                 | الإدارة          | Full platform access                      |
| customer              | العميل           | Own projects, orders, payments            |
| contractor            | المقاول          | Assigned projects, materials, withdrawals |
| supervising_architect | المهندس المشرف   | Supervised projects, field engineers      |
| field_engineer        | المهندس الميداني | Assigned tasks, field reports             |

## Input Validation

- All inputs validated via Form Request classes
- Never use raw user input in SQL queries
- XSS prevention in all responses
- CSRF protection on state-changing endpoints

## File Upload Security

- Validate MIME type server-side
- Validate file size server-side
- Store via Laravel filesystem (disk: local/s3)
- Never execute uploaded files

## Payment Security

- All payment operations server-side only
- Idempotent payment endpoints
- Transaction logging for all financial operations
- Withdrawal verification workflow

## Workflow Security

- Status transitions validated server-side against workflow configuration
- Approval rules checked before status changes
- Audit trail for all workflow mutations

